Pull, Tag, Push Docker Image and Create New Image with Installed Software
Aim

To demonstrate how to pull a Docker image, tag it, push it to Docker Hub, install software inside a running container, verify the installation, and save the changes using Docker commit.

Step 1: Pull Alpine Image
docker pull alpine
Step 2: Tag the Alpine Image
docker tag alpine dishatribedy/alpine-php:v1
Step 3: Login to Docker Hub
docker login
Step 4: Push Image to Docker Hub
docker push dishatribedy/alpine-php:v1
Step 5: Run the Image Interactively
docker run -it alpine sh
Step 6: Update Package Index
apk update
Step 7: Install PHP
apk add php
Step 8: Verify PHP Installation
php -v
Step 9: Exit the Container
exit
Step 10: Commit Container Changes to New Image
docker commit fab6f3a8adc8 dishatribedy/alpine-php-installed:v1
Result

The Alpine Docker image was successfully pulled, tagged, pushed to Docker Hub, and modified by installing PHP inside a container. The changes were saved as a new Docker image using the docker commit command.

